  <gco:CharacterString>An orthoimage is remotely sensed image data in which displacement of features in the image caused by terrain relief and sensor orientation have been mathematically removed. Orthoimagery combines the image characteristics of a photograph with the geometric qualities of a map. For this dataset, the true color orthoimages were produced at Half Foot GSD.</gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:abstract>          <gmd:purpose>             <gco:CharacterString>Provide high
